==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congressional
<hw>Con*gres"sion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to a congress, especially, to the Congress of the United
States; <as>as, <ex>congressional</ex> debates</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Congressional</qex> and official labor.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Congressional District</b></col>, <cd>one of the
divisions into which a State is periodically divided (according to
population), each of which is entitled to elect a Representative to the
Congress of the United States.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congressive</ent>⟦br⟧
